============================================================

All 33 tests still pass. Here's what the self-review addressed:

**Fixed:**
1. `[jJ]` inconsistency in `POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` — removed redundant character classes since the `/i` flag already handles case (`wymiesza[jJ]` → `wymieszaj`, `miesza[jJ]` → `mieszaj`)
2. Clarified the comment on the `closeCompetitors` path — it now clearly states "collapse to one" rather than implying "keep", and added a note that the ≤10 span path intentionally falls through keeping all candidates

**Accepted as-is:**
- No new unit tests added — this is an iteration loop context where real-file tests in `tools/title-loop` serve that purpose
- The 4-word minimum in `looksLikeCookingInstruction` silently neutralizes very short Polish imperatives — this is an accepted tradeoff (3-word imperatives like "Dodaj cebulę sól" are rare in practice and may legitimately be ambiguous)
- The ` : ` separator in the word-count exception is intentional — colon-separated multi-part titles exist in the corpus
