{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SBqTTUQzQuHUWyJud6ucnF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 33 tests pass. Here's a summary of the three changes implemented:\n\n**Change 1 — Polish cooking instruction filter** (`looksLikeCookingInstruction`): Added `POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` regex covering common Polish imperative verbs (`podawaj`, `dodaj`, `smaż`, `gotuj`, etc.). Lines like `\"Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno\"` are now filtered as cooking instructions.\n\n**Change 2 — Position-based tiebreak for zero-ALL_CAPS case** (multi-title guard): Added an `else` branch for when no ALL_CAPS candidates survive. When surviving candidates are spread >10 lines apart (indicating body-text leakage), it keeps only the earliest candidate (with a 3-position tolerance for higher-scoring competitors). When candidates are close together (≤10 lines apart), all are kept — preserving the existing multi-recipe behavior that the `First Recipe + Second Recipe` test relies on.\n\n**Change 3 — Word count filter** (`passesHardFilters`): Lines with ≥8 words are rejected as body text, with an exception for multi-title compounds containing ` + `, ` : `, or ` & ` separators. This filters long cooking instructions like `\"No potelni rozprowadż oliwę z oliwek i smaż crosnek na duzym ogr\"` (12 words)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":285,"cache_read_input_tokens":68670,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":285},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8522d0c9-fb93-4365-9c6c-c3c9ffbbbc7e","uuid":"32299808-02e9-4375-b8f8-49310c34e099"}
